ce:section.ce:para:
To examine the chemical composition and different kinds of bonds in the produced CDs, an XPS elemental analysis was performed. The XPS survey scan spectrum of the CDs is shown in Fig. 3
                        a. Three peaks at 283.1, 397.8, and 529.9 eV correspond to C1s, N1s, and O1s with component ratios of 70.14, 7.17, and 22.68 %, respectively (Table 1
                        ). The deconvoluted XPS spectra of C1s, N1s, and O1s of the developed CDs are shown in Fig. 3b–d. The high-resolution XPS spectrum of C1s (Fig. 3b) is fitted with three peaks at 282.5, 283.9, and 285.7 eV, ascribed to CC, CN, and CO, respectively. Fig. 3c displays the high-resolution spectrum of N1s with two peaks of binding energies 397.6 and 399.7 eV, suggesting the presence of CN and NH bonds. The existence of CO and COH bonds were proven by the two peaks at 528.9 and 530.2 eV in the high resolution XPS spectrum of O1s (Fig. 3d).
